<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-17T10:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-17T10:41:00-05:00" n="561" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/552</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-17T17:00:00+01:19">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.23 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3194. My 3189, June 16, 1 p.m., in regard to the Dutch East Indian
                                convoy. The French Minister without instructions from his Government
                                has today addressed a note to the Dutch Government asking whether it
                                will give France the same assurances that it has given Great Britain
                                in answer to the British note of June 7 telegraphed you in my 3163,
                                June 13, 4 p.m. He also asks what these assurances are. He hopes to
                                see <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LJJ1">Loudon</persName>
                                tomorrow and get his answer.</p>
                            <p>Do you wish me to take similar or other steps in the matter?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>